Script 1: I am now going to ask questions about your pregnancy. We will do our best to keep your answers confidential. By providing honest answers, you may be able to help us understand the health issues in your community better.
When did you deliver?
Was the baby born alive?
How much did your baby weigh after birth? (Kg)
Is your baby alive now?
How much does your baby weigh now? (Kg)
Script 2: Now I would like to talk to you about your antenatal care for your recent pregnancy.
Where did you give birth?
Specify the other delivery location
Who assisted with the delivery?
Specify the other person who assisted in delivering
Was your labor induced?
Did you get a cesarean section?
Were there any complications during delivery?

hint.text: Explain and review options with client and select all that apply.

prompt.text: Specify other complication
Script 3: Now I would like to talk to you about breastfeeding.
Did you ever breastfeed after this delivery?
Are you still breastfeeding?
For how long has this child been breastfed?
Script 4: Now I would like to talk about your health and your child’s health.
Were you tested for HIV between the time you were tested for the study and now?

hint.text: (i.e. after enrolling while at the clinic if you did not receive a home visit,  or after the home visit)

prompt.text: Where were you tested for HIV?
Other location
What was the result of your most recent HIV test?
Have you ever enrolled or registered into the HIV comprehensive care clinic (CCC)?
Do you know your CD4 test results?
What was the result of your most recent CD4 test?
Were you prescribed medicine to manage your HIV infection or protect your child from HIV?
Were you prescribed triple ART?
Were you prescribed AZT/ZDV during your pregnancy?
For how long were you prescribed ART treatment?
Are you currently taking ART treatment you were prescribed?
Did you receive a single dose of Nevirapine and/or a dose of AZT/ZDV + 3TC during labor?

hint.text: Select yes if any of these were received.

prompt.text: Were you given AZT/ZDV and 3TC to take during the next 7 days after delivery?
Was your child prescribed Nevirapine syrup for 6 weeks after delivery or until after breastfeeding (or in rare circumstances Lamivudine)?
Is your child currently taking Nevirapine syrup?
Sometimes it is difficult to make infants consume Nevirapine. Has the child missed any doses during the past 7 days?
Script 5: Now, I would like to ask you questions about your relationship
You reported being in a relationship with a male partner when you enrolled in this study. Has your relationship with this partner changed in any of the following ways since your last study visit?

hint.text: Review all options with client and choose all that apply:

prompt.text: Specify other change.
Did your relationship end because of something involving participation in this study?
What about the study caused your relationship to end?
Specify other reason.
Thank you for your time in answering these questions.
